## Review Guidelines

### Correctness & Safety
- Ignored errors (`_ = err`); missing error wraps with context
- Race conditions; incorrect mutex/channel usage
- Hardcoded secrets in source or config

### Go idioms
- Context not passed or cancelled; missing timeouts on HTTP clients
- Defer in loops; pointer to range variable bugs
- interface{} / any overuse hiding contracts

### Performance
- Allocations in hot paths; unnecessary string concatenation in loops
- Goroutine leaks; unbounded channel sends

## Scoring

- **90-100**: Clean code, no significant issues
- **70-89**: Minor issues only
- **50-69**: Moderate issues
- **30-49**: Serious issues
- **0-29**: Critical issues requiring immediate fix

